    "faq_custom_wyTcTx": {
      "type": "FAQ-custom",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UakJ7C": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can stainless steel pans be nonstick?",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes! When properly preheated and used correctly, stainless steel creates a natural nonstick surface without any chemicals.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_bLfiCV": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What's the real benefit of 5-ply?",
            "row_content": "<p>the main advantage is perfectly even heating. Standard pans often have hot spots that burn food. Our 5-ply construction layers stainless steel around a core of aluminum, spreading heat evenly across the entire cooking surface. This means no more scorched sauces and perfectly seared meats every time.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_B3XwFW": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why is it more expensive?",
            "row_content": "<p>You're paying for long-term performance and durability. The 5-ply build is engineered to resist warping and will last a lifetime, unlike cheaper pans that need frequent replacing. It's an investment that actually saves you money over the years while making cooking easier</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_Mwhc6d": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is the stainless steel surface really safe?",
            "row_content": "<p>Completely. The stainless steel cooking surface is non-toxic and won't react with acidic foods. Unlike some non-stick pans, there's no risk of harmful chemicals flaking into your food, even at high heat. It's a safe, reliable choice for healthy cooking.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
